    • Constructor Detail

      • Result

        public Result​(Date date,
              String state,
              int positive,
              int hospitalizations,
              int death)
        Creates a Result object. Each Result object represents one record returned by the database query.
        Parameters:
        date - date of report
        state - state of report
        positive - number of positive cases reported in selected state on given day
        hospitalizations - number of hospitalizations reported in selected state on given day
        death - number of deaths reported in selected state on given day

      • Result

        public Result​(int id,
              Date date,
              String state,
              int positive,
              int hospitalizations,
              int death)
        Creates a Result object with a specified ID. Each Result object represents one record returned by the database query.
        Parameters:
        id - the ID (primary key) of the Result object (database record)
        date - date of report
        state - state of report
        positive - number of positive cases reported in selected state on given day
        hospitalizations - number of hospitalizations reported in selected state on given day
        death - number of deaths reported in selected state on given day
